<br>
I've got a level 46 paladin with 200 2hblunt, 195+ 1hslash, 195+ 2hslash, 195+ 1hblunt, and about 60 piercing.  His Granite Face Grinder is the best weapon he's able to use right now, but it doesn't mean something better might not appear. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>57 Halfling Shaman
<br><img src=http://www.tbp.mb.ca/~stimpy/everquest/JuujuuHalflingSentry.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarathena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arathena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Valkyrie of Innoruuk</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/4/01 1:47:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what weapon should SK use?  or skill?</span><hr size=1> 1HB is an important one, right now, the end of its line exemplified by the MoSS and Ebon Mace. Best way to deal with this that I've found is to pull out some Fine steel or the like before 10, be at 50 or so, and then just wait till you have a good weapon to use it with. Both the MoSS and Ebon mace are quick weapons, and a night or three with a friendly enchanter and Swift like the Wind will pull it to par with your level very qickly.<br>
<br>
1HS is a solid midlevel skill right now, for weapons along the lines of the SSoY, and Wurmslayer. Best weapon for developing this is the 5/19 Bladed Thulian Claw. Cheap as dirt and fast as hell's vengeance.<br>
<br>
2HB has two words: Deathbringer's Rod. The Poison Wind Censer is also a fine weapon, though the AoE DoT proc hurts it in a number of dungeon situations. This skill can be developed by the Abandoned Orc Shovel, which is a free item laying on the ground in Lake Rathe. Just have a higher level friend gank all the orcs in the appropriate camp, and pick it up, and be aware that it's No Drop.<br>
<br>
2HS is probably what you'll actually wind up using from 15-40, when you should upgarde to a MoSS, be it the old fashioned Dark Reaver, a Runic Carver, or even a higher end weapon, like a Throneblade or an Argent Defender.<br>
<br>
Piercing is one of those... neeeh, only if I have time to spare and I'm not vital to the group skills. There just aren't currently many high piercers to look forwards to, although the Dragoon Dirk makes a great newbie weapon, and a Stalagterror Spine Spear a fine mid range alternative. There's a sort of inherent promise in the creation of 2H piercers though, so this may turn out to be worthwhile.<br>
<br>
Archery, well, fuggedaboudit. It's just not very valuable to a SK after 9, and bluntly, with a skill cap of 75, not worth the weight of the arrows let alone the bow for damage in the kite back to the group. <br>
<br>
Anything I'm missing? I hope not. <br>
<br>
As for spell skills.. keep them all up.  <p><center>Arathena Dracheseele<br>
